WEBVTT

1
00:00:11.820 --> 00:00:14.084
I'm a professional troublemaker.
我是个专业的麻烦制造者。

2
00:00:14.264 --> 00:00:15.629
(Laughter)
(笑声)

3
00:00:15.729 --> 00:00:21.749
As my job is to critique the world,
因为我的工作就是批判世界，

4
00:00:21.878 --> 00:00:25.065
the shoddy systems and the people who refuse to do better,
批判劣质的系统与不求上进的人，

5
00:00:25.811 --> 00:00:28.986
as a writer, as a speaker, as a shady Nigerian --
作为一名作家、演讲家 以及一名“臭名昭著”的尼日利亚人——

6
00:00:28.826 --> 00:00:29.574
(Laughter)
（笑声）

7
00:00:29.574 --> 00:00:33.779
I feel like my purpose is to be this cat.
我觉得我的工作 就和图中这只猫差不多。

8
00:00:33.779 --> 00:00:35.771
(Laughter)
（笑声） （图片：自认清高的艺术家）

9
00:00:35.771 --> 00:00:39.036
I am the person who is looking at other people,
我就是那种挑剔别人生活的人，

10
00:00:38.919 --> 00:00:40.483
like, "I need you to fix it."
总想着 “我需要你改一改。”

11
00:00:41.151 --> 00:00:42.306
That is me.
这就是我。

12
00:00:42.330 --> 00:00:46.511
I want us to leave this world better than we found it.
我希望我们可以 让这个世界变得更好。

13
00:00:47.054 --> 00:00:49.820
And how I choose to effect change
我选择改变世界的方式

14
00:00:49.844 --> 00:00:51.257
is by speaking up,
是畅所欲言，

15
00:00:51.281 --> 00:00:53.665
by being the first and by being the domino.
通过当第一张多米诺骨牌。

16
00:00:54.846 --> 00:00:57.211
For a line of dominoes to fall,
为了让一排骨牌倒下，

17
00:00:57.143 --> 00:00:59.384
one has to fall first,
必须有一个先倒下，

18
00:00:58.853 --> 00:01:01.591
which then leaves the other choiceless to do the same.
剩下的骨牌别无选择， 就会跟着倒下。

19
00:01:03.057 --> 00:01:04.659
And that domino that falls,
有了那张倒下的骨牌，

20
00:01:04.683 --> 00:01:06.941
we're hoping that, OK,
我们希望

21
00:01:06.965 --> 00:01:10.417
the next person that sees this is inspired to be a domino.
下个看到这个情况的人会被激励， 也成为一张骨牌。

22
00:01:11.935 --> 00:01:15.123
Being the domino, for me, looks like speaking up
对我而言，作为骨牌就要公开表态，

23
00:01:14.843 --> 00:01:16.765
and doing the things that are really difficult,
就要迎难而上，

24
00:01:16.765 --> 00:01:19.234
especially when they are needed,
特别是当人们需要 有人挺身而出的时候，

25
00:01:19.527 --> 00:01:21.889
with the hope that others will follow suit.
希望其他人也能效仿。

26
00:01:22.861 --> 00:01:25.420
And here's the thing: I'm the person who says
此外还有一点： 我就是那种会说出

27
00:01:25.444 --> 00:01:28.901
what you might be thinking but dared not to say.
想说但不敢说的话的人。

28
00:01:28.925 --> 00:01:31.692
A lot of times people think that we're fearless,
人们经常会觉得 我们这种人是无所畏惧的，

29
00:01:31.716 --> 00:01:33.694
the people who do this, we're fearless.
做这种事的人是无所畏惧的。

30
00:01:32.994 --> 00:01:34.472
We're not fearless.
我们并不是无所畏惧。

31
00:01:34.900 --> 00:01:37.374
We're not unafraid of the consequences
我们并不是不怕这些后果，

32
00:01:36.978 --> 00:01:39.307
or the sacrifices that we have to make
也不是不惧怕

33
00:01:39.632 --> 00:01:41.628
by speaking truth to power.
宣扬真理后的牺牲。

34
00:01:41.652 --> 00:01:43.851
What happens is, we feel like we have to,
事实上，我们觉得这是我们的义务，

35
00:01:43.875 --> 00:01:46.478
because there are too few people in the world
因为在这个世界

36
00:01:46.502 --> 00:01:48.129
willing to be the domino,
愿意当骨牌的人太少，

37
00:01:48.153 --> 00:01:50.511
too few people willing to take that fall.
鲜有人愿意第一个倒下。

38
00:01:50.535 --> 00:01:52.257
We're not doing it without fear.
我们这么做不是不会恐惧。

39
00:01:52.281 --> 00:01:53.653
Now, let's talk about fear.
现在，我们讲一讲恐惧。

40
00:01:53.992 --> 00:01:56.044
I knew exactly what I wanted to be when I grew up.
我曾经很清楚长大后想做什么，

41
00:01:56.585 --> 00:01:58.523
I was like, "I'm going to be a doctor!"
“我要成为一位医生!”

42
00:01:58.547 --> 00:02:00.109
Doctor Luvvie was the dream.
当上医生是我曾经的梦想，

43
00:02:00.696 --> 00:02:02.949
I was Doc McStuffins before it was a thing.
在《小医师大玩偶》流行起来之前 我就在扮演医师。

44
00:02:02.973 --> 00:02:04.172
(Laughter)
（笑声）

45
00:02:04.196 --> 00:02:06.403
And I remember when I went to college,
我记得我上大学的时候，

46
00:02:06.427 --> 00:02:10.133
my freshman year, I had to take Chemistry 101
我大一的时候， 必须上化学基础这门课，

47
00:02:09.927 --> 00:02:11.761
for my premed major.
为了我的预科主修做准备。

48
00:02:12.935 --> 00:02:16.003
I got the first and last D of my academic career.
我拿了学术生涯中唯一的一个D。

49
00:02:15.653 --> 00:02:17.607
(Laughter)
（笑声）

50
00:02:17.725 --> 00:02:20.297
So I went to my advisor, and I was like,
于是我去找学校辅导员说：

51
00:02:20.321 --> 00:02:22.575
"OK, let's drop the premed,
“我放弃医学院预科了，

52
00:02:22.599 --> 00:02:24.822
because this doctor thing is not going to work,
因为我不是当医生的料，

53
00:02:24.846 --> 00:02:26.590
because I don't even like hospitals.
因为我根本就不喜欢医院。

54
00:02:26.614 --> 00:02:27.765
So ..."
所以...“

55
00:02:27.789 --> 00:02:28.820
(Laughter)
（笑声）

56
00:02:28.844 --> 00:02:30.972
"Let's just consider that done for."
“还是算了吧。”

57
00:02:31.548 --> 00:02:33.968
And that same semester, I started blogging.
也是在那个学期，我开始写博客。

58
00:02:33.992 --> 00:02:35.421
That was 2003.
那是2003年。

59
00:02:35.445 --> 00:02:38.304
So as that one dream was ending, another was beginning.
当一个梦想结束的时候， 另外一个梦想开始了。

60
00:02:38.328 --> 00:02:41.897
And then what was a cute hobby became my full-time job
后来，当我2010年失去了 市场营销工作的时候，

61
00:02:41.921 --> 00:02:44.816
when I lost my marketing job in 2010.
这个可爱的爱好 就成为了我全职的工作。

62
00:02:44.840 --> 00:02:48.214
But it still took me two more years to say, "I'm a writer."
但我花了两年多时间才能说： “我是个作家。”

63
00:02:48.238 --> 00:02:53.456
Nine years after I had started writing, before I said, "I'm a writer,"
在我写作了九年之后我才说， “我是个作家。“

64
00:02:53.480 --> 00:02:56.279
because I was afraid of what happens
因为我害怕

65
00:02:55.949 --> 00:02:58.155
without 401ks,
没有退休金的后果，

66
00:02:58.343 --> 00:03:00.851
without, "How am I going to keep up my shoe habit?
我害怕我不能 继续保持买鞋的习惯，

67
00:03:00.875 --> 00:03:02.041
That's important to me."
那对我很重要。

68
00:03:01.219 --> 00:03:02.813
(Laughter)
（笑声）

69
00:03:02.813 --> 00:03:05.848
So it took me that long to own this thing
所以我需要花很长的时间

70
00:03:05.848 --> 00:03:07.798
that was what my purpose was.
去了解我的目的是什么。

71
00:03:07.885 --> 00:03:09.320
And then I realized,
然后我意识到，

72
00:03:09.344 --> 00:03:11.654
fear has a very concrete power
恐惧是一股非常具体的力量，

73
00:03:11.678 --> 00:03:15.870
of keeping us from doing and saying the things that are our purpose.
会阻止我们说出和践行 我们真正的目的。

74
00:03:16.642 --> 00:03:18.316
And I was like, "You know what?
于是我想，“你知道吗？

75
00:03:17.988 --> 00:03:20.972
I'm not going to let fear rule my life.
我不会让恐惧主宰我的生活。

76
00:03:20.966 --> 00:03:24.388
I'm not going to let fear dictate what I do."
我不会让恐惧支配我的所作所为。”

77
00:03:23.941 --> 00:03:27.100
And then all of these awesome things started happening,
于是所有奇妙的事情开始发生了，

78
00:03:27.420 --> 00:03:28.999
and dominoes started to fall.
骨牌开始倒下了。

79
00:03:29.670 --> 00:03:32.349
So when I realized that, I was like, "OK, 2015,
当我意识到的时候， 我开始想，“好，2015年

80
00:03:32.373 --> 00:03:33.638
I turned 30,
我30岁了，

81
00:03:33.662 --> 00:03:35.850
it's going to be my year of 'Do it anyway.'
这将是我 ‘不顾一切‘ 的一年

82
00:03:35.874 --> 00:03:38.899
Anything that scares me, I'm going to actively pursue it."
我会积极地去追求 任何令我恐惧的事情。”

83
00:03:39.487 --> 00:03:41.677
So, I'm a Capricorn.
我是个摩羯座，

84
00:03:41.701 --> 00:03:43.823
I like my feel solidly on the ground.
我喜欢脚踏实地的感觉。

85
00:03:44.991 --> 00:03:47.842
I decided to take my first-ever solo vacation,
我决定开启人生的首次个人旅行，

86
00:03:47.866 --> 00:03:50.647
and it was out of the country to the Dominican Republic.
我决定去多米尼加共和国。

87
00:03:51.647 --> 00:03:54.242
So on my birthday, what did I do?
那么在我生日的那一天， 我做了什么？

88
00:03:54.266 --> 00:03:56.731
I went ziplining through the forests of Punta Cana.
我通过索道 穿越蓬塔·卡纳森林。

89
00:03:56.926 --> 00:03:59.298
And for some odd reason, I had on business casual.
因为某些奇怪的原因， 我穿了商务装。

90
00:03:59.937 --> 00:04:01.119
Don't ask why.
不要问我为什么。

91
00:04:00.797 --> 00:04:03.133
(Laughter)
（笑声）

92
00:04:03.369 --> 00:04:05.223
And I had an incredible time.
我度过了特别棒的时光。

93
00:04:05.247 --> 00:04:07.383
Also, I don't like being submerged in water.
我不喜欢潜水。

94
00:04:07.407 --> 00:04:09.761
I like to be, again, on solid ground.
再说一次， 我喜欢脚踏实地。

95
00:04:09.785 --> 00:04:14.331
So I went to Mexico and swam with dolphins underwater.
所以我去了墨西哥， 在水下和海豚游泳。

96
00:04:14.821 --> 00:04:17.291
And then the cool thing that I did also that year
那一年，我还做了一件超酷的事情，

97
00:04:17.476 --> 00:04:19.565
that was my mountain
那是我的人生巅峰——

98
00:04:19.589 --> 00:04:21.479
was I wrote my book,
我写了一本书，

99
00:04:21.503 --> 00:04:23.555
"I'm Judging You: The Do-Better Manual,"
《我在评判你：如何做得更好》

100
00:04:23.579 --> 00:04:24.732
And I had to own --
所以我现在应该算——

101
00:04:24.756 --> 00:04:25.770
(Applause)
（掌声）

102
00:04:25.794 --> 00:04:27.591
that whole writing thing now, right?
掌握写作的能力了，对吧？

103
00:04:27.615 --> 00:04:28.858
Yes.
是的。

104
00:04:28.882 --> 00:04:31.910
But the very anti-me thing that I did that year
但在那一年，我做的 最非常“反我”的事情，

105
00:04:31.934 --> 00:04:33.726
that scared the crap out of me --
简直要吓死我了——

106
00:04:34.726 --> 00:04:36.230
I went skydiving.
我去跳伞了。

107
00:04:37.359 --> 00:04:39.167
We're about to fall out of the plane.
我们正要从飞机里跳下去的时候,

108
00:04:38.881 --> 00:04:41.525
I was like, "I've done some stupid things in life. This is one of them."
我在想， “这绝对是我这辈子做过的蠢事之一。”

109
00:04:41.525 --> 00:04:42.777
(Laughter)
（笑）

110
00:04:42.777 --> 00:04:45.061
And then we come falling down to Earth,
接下来我们就向地面坠落，

111
00:04:45.650 --> 00:04:48.893
and I literally lose my breath as I see Earth, and I was like,
我看着地面， 我简直无法呼吸，

112
00:04:48.917 --> 00:04:51.567
"I just fell out of a perfectly good plane on purpose."
我在想，“我刚刚故意从一架 完好无损的飞机上跳下来了！”

113
00:04:51.591 --> 00:04:52.615
(Laughter)
（笑）

114
00:04:52.639 --> 00:04:54.081
"What is wrong with me?!"
“我有毛病吗？！”

115
00:04:53.859 --> 00:04:55.886
But then I looked down at the beauty,
但当我俯视地表美景时，

116
00:04:55.886 --> 00:04:58.549
and I was like, "This is the best thing I could have done.
我在想， ‘“这是我做过的最好的事情，

117
00:04:58.819 --> 00:05:01.052
This was an amazing decision."
这是一个超棒的决定。”

118
00:05:01.076 --> 00:05:03.925
And I think about the times when I have to speak truth.
我回想起需要 说出实话的那些时刻。

119
00:05:03.949 --> 00:05:07.260
It feels like I am falling out of that plane.
那感觉就像正从飞机上掉下来，

120
00:05:07.284 --> 00:05:10.139
It feels like that moment when I'm at the edge of the plane,
就像我在飞机边缘的那一刻，

121
00:05:09.926 --> 00:05:11.624
and I'm like, "You shouldn't do this,"
我告诉自己，“你不应该这么做，”

122
00:05:11.624 --> 00:05:14.274
but then I do it anyway, because I realize I have to.
但无论如何我还是做了， 因为我意识到自己必须去做。

123
00:05:15.494 --> 00:05:17.180
Sitting at the edge of that plane
对我来说，坐在飞机边缘，

124
00:05:16.938 --> 00:05:19.841
and kind of staying on that plane is comfort to me.
或者说呆在飞机上是很舒服的。

125
00:05:19.841 --> 00:05:21.928
And I feel like every day that I'm speaking truth
我感觉，在我诉说真相，

126
00:05:21.928 --> 00:05:24.327
against institutions and people who are bigger than me
和那些比我强大的机构和人，

127
00:05:24.327 --> 00:05:27.200
and just forces that are more powerful than me,
以及那些更强大的势力抗衡的每一天。

128
00:05:27.531 --> 00:05:29.590
I feel like I'm falling out of that plane.
都仿佛从那架飞机上掉下来一般。

129
00:05:29.614 --> 00:05:31.720
But I realize comfort is overrated.
但我意识到， 舒适感其实被高估了。

130
00:05:31.744 --> 00:05:34.454
Because being quiet is comfortable.
因为沉默是最舒适的。

131
00:05:34.478 --> 00:05:37.799
Keeping things the way they've been is comfortable.
不去改变才是舒适的。

132
00:05:37.823 --> 00:05:40.519
And all comfort has done is maintain the status quo.
但是舒适感能带给我们的 只有维护现状而已。

133
00:05:40.543 --> 00:05:43.225
So we've got to get comfortable with being uncomfortable
所以我们应该通过 在必要的时候说出严峻的现实

134
00:05:42.732 --> 00:05:45.480
by speaking these hard truths when they're necessary.
来学会走出自己的舒适区。

135
00:05:46.655 --> 00:05:47.956
And I --
而且我——

136
00:05:47.980 --> 00:05:51.151
(Applause)
（掌声）

137
00:05:50.916 --> 00:05:54.809
And for me, though, I realize that I have to speak these truths,
我也意识到了坦白真相的重要性，

138
00:05:54.926 --> 00:05:56.875
because honesty is so important to me.
因为诚实对于我来说非常重要。

139
00:05:56.899 --> 00:05:59.142
My integrity is something I hold dear.
我珍惜我的正直。

140
00:05:58.821 --> 00:06:01.285
Justice -- I don't think justice should be an option.
正义—— 我不认为正义是一个选项。

141
00:06:01.731 --> 00:06:03.211
We should always have justice.
我们需要一直保持公平正义。

142
00:06:03.235 --> 00:06:06.573
Also, I believe in shea butter as a core value, and --
不过，我相信 乳木果油也十分重要——

143
00:06:06.597 --> 00:06:07.895
(Laughter)
（笑声）

144
00:06:07.919 --> 00:06:11.509
and I think the world would be better if we were more moisturized.
因为如果我们更加滋润， 世界就会变得更好。

145
00:06:12.303 --> 00:06:15.115
But besides that, with these as my core values,
但除此之外，

146
00:06:12.978 --> 00:06:16.113
I have to speak the truth.
我的核心价值观是： 我必须讲出事实。

147
00:06:16.438 --> 00:06:18.293
I have no other choice in the matter.
在这个问题上我没有其他的选择。

148
00:06:18.317 --> 00:06:20.710
But people like me, the professional troublemakers,
但像我这样的人， 专业的麻烦制造者，

149
00:06:20.734 --> 00:06:24.033
should not be the only ones who are committed to being these dominoes
不应该只有我们为成为骨牌献身，

150
00:06:22.904 --> 00:06:24.447
who are always falling out of planes
不应该只有我们 总是从飞机上跳下来，

151
00:06:24.447 --> 00:06:27.516
or being the first one to take this hit.
不应该只有我们成为靶子。

152
00:06:27.777 --> 00:06:30.106
People are so afraid of these acute consequences,
人们惧怕严重的后果，

153
00:06:29.696 --> 00:06:32.945
not realizing that there are many times when we walk in rooms
所以没有意识到，很多时候， 当我们走进房间时，

154
00:06:32.945 --> 00:06:35.832
and we are some of the most powerful people in those rooms --
我们是房间里最强大的一批人——

155
00:06:35.832 --> 00:06:38.503
we might be the second-most powerful, third-most powerful.
或者可能是第二强大、 第三强大的人。

156
00:06:38.503 --> 00:06:41.616
And I firmly believe that our job in those times
并且我坚信那时我们的任务

157
00:06:41.887 --> 00:06:43.936
is to disrupt what is happening.
是去中止正在发生的事。

158
00:06:43.960 --> 00:06:46.059
And then if we're not the most powerful,
如果我们不是最强大的人，

159
00:06:45.753 --> 00:06:48.180
if two more of us band together,
只要有更多的人加入我们，

160
00:06:48.333 --> 00:06:49.790
it makes us powerful.
我们就会变得更强大。

161
00:06:49.814 --> 00:06:52.277
It's like cosigning the woman in the meeting,
比如在开会时联合所有女性，

162
00:06:51.960 --> 00:06:55.098
you know, the woman who can't seem to get her word out,
我们要让那些不敢发声的女性，

163
00:06:55.220 --> 00:06:58.624
or just making sure that other person who can't make a point
那些不敢发表看法的人

164
00:06:58.648 --> 00:06:59.957
is being heard.
能被倾听。

165
00:06:59.981 --> 00:07:03.235
Our job is to make sure they have room for that.
我们的任务是为了 确保她们的这一权益。

166
00:07:03.259 --> 00:07:05.367
Everyone's well-being is community business.
社会的目标就是确保每个人的幸福。

167
00:07:05.391 --> 00:07:07.614
If we made that a point, we'd understand that,
如果我们明确了这一点， 我们就会了解到，

168
00:07:07.638 --> 00:07:09.300
for the times when we need help,
当我们需要帮助的时候，

169
00:07:08.905 --> 00:07:10.373
we wouldn't have to look around so hard
如果我们曾经对他人施以援手，

170
00:07:10.373 --> 00:07:12.457
if we made sure we were somebody else's help.
就不必艰难地四处求助。

171
00:07:14.133 --> 00:07:15.903
And there are times when I feel like
有时候，我在公共场合

172
00:07:15.927 --> 00:07:19.947
I have taken very public tumbles and falls,
会感到十分受挫，

173
00:07:19.971 --> 00:07:22.652
like the time when I was asked to speak at a conference,
比如有一次， 我受邀去会议上发表演讲，

174
00:07:22.676 --> 00:07:25.669
and they wanted me to pay my way there.
他们想让我自付差旅费。

175
00:07:26.161 --> 00:07:27.524
And then I did some research
然后我做了些调查，

176
00:07:27.548 --> 00:07:30.651
and found out the white men who spoke there got compensated
发现在那儿演讲的 白人男性都拿到了酬劳，

177
00:07:30.675 --> 00:07:32.572
and got their travel paid for.
并报销了他们的差旅费。

178
00:07:32.596 --> 00:07:35.620
The white women who spoke there got their travel paid for.
在那儿演讲的白人女性 至少也拿到了差旅费。

179
00:07:35.644 --> 00:07:39.926
The black women who spoke there were expected to actually pay to speak there.
而黑人女性，却需要自费演讲。

180
00:07:39.950 --> 00:07:41.648
And I was like, "What do I do?"
我就在想，“我该怎么办？“

181
00:07:42.237 --> 00:07:44.978
And I knew that if I spoke up about this publicly,
我知道如果将这件事公之于众，

182
00:07:44.987 --> 00:07:46.488
I could face financial loss.
我可能会面对财务损失。

183
00:07:46.979 --> 00:07:49.995
But then I also understood that my silence serves no one.
但是我也知道 我的沉默不会帮助任何人。

184
00:07:50.478 --> 00:07:53.582
So I fearfully spoke up about it publicly,
所以尽管心中十分忐忑， 我还是公开地谈论了这件事情。

185
00:07:53.606 --> 00:07:56.225
and other women started coming out to talk about,
之后其他女性也开始站出来谈论，

186
00:07:55.951 --> 00:07:58.790
"I, too, have faced this type of pay inequality."
“我也面对过这种不公平的待遇。”

187
00:07:58.825 --> 00:08:01.930
And it started a conversation about discriminatory pay practices
于是我们开始讨论那个会议的

188
00:08:01.954 --> 00:08:04.469
that this conference was participating in.
歧视性报酬。

189
00:08:04.493 --> 00:08:06.885
I felt like I was the domino
当我读到一位公众人物

190
00:08:06.909 --> 00:08:09.632
the time I read a disturbing memoir by a public figure
带有歧视性的回忆录 并写了一些读后感时，

191
00:08:09.656 --> 00:08:11.023
and wrote a piece about it.
我觉得我成了一张骨牌，

192
00:08:11.471 --> 00:08:14.968
I knew this person was more powerful than me and could impact my career,
我知道这个人比我更强大， 他可能会影响我的事业，

193
00:08:14.992 --> 00:08:16.810
but I was like, "I've got to do this.
但我想，“我得做这件事。

194
00:08:16.834 --> 00:08:20.235
I've got to sit at the edge of this plane," maybe for two hours.
我得坐在“飞机”的边缘， 想了大概两个小时，

195
00:08:19.352 --> 00:08:22.469
And I did. And I pressed "Publish," and I ran away.
最后决定放手一搏。 我按了“发布”键，然后溜了。

196
00:08:22.722 --> 00:08:23.759
(Laughter)
（笑声）

197
00:08:23.783 --> 00:08:25.695
And I came back to a viral post
然后我发现这篇文章 收到了极高的关注，

198
00:08:25.719 --> 00:08:29.321
and people being like, "Oh my God, I'm so glad somebody finally said this."
人们在说，“天哪，我很开心 终于有个人说这个了。“

199
00:08:28.981 --> 00:08:30.337
And it started a conversation
然后它开启了一场

200
00:08:30.881 --> 00:08:33.673
about mental health and self-care,
关于精神健康和自我照顾的讨论，

201
00:08:33.697 --> 00:08:35.548
and I was like, "OK. Alright.
我想，“好啊，

202
00:08:35.572 --> 00:08:38.956
This thing that I'm doing, I guess, alright, it's doing something."
我猜我正在做的这件事情， 正在产生影响。”

203
00:08:38.980 --> 00:08:42.400
And then so many people have been the domino
然后当很多人开始讨论

204
00:08:43.242 --> 00:08:47.580
when they talk about how they've been assaulted by powerful men.
自己怎么被位高权重的男性 抨击的时候，他们也成为了骨牌。

205
00:08:47.604 --> 00:08:52.026
And it's made millions of women join in and say, "Me Too."
然后数百万女性也加入进来， 并说出，“我也是。”

206
00:08:52.050 --> 00:08:54.906
So, a shout-out to Tarana Burke for igniting that movement.
在此，要感谢 塔拉娜·伯克点燃了这场运动。

207
00:08:54.930 --> 00:09:01.555
(Applause)
（掌声）

208
00:09:01.579 --> 00:09:06.321
People and systems count on our silence to keep us exactly where we are.
大众和体制在依靠 我们的沉默去维持现状。

209
00:09:07.826 --> 00:09:13.417
Now, being the domino sometimes comes down to being exactly who you are.
但有的时候成为骨牌就是在做自己。

210
00:09:13.835 --> 00:09:16.924
So, I've been a shady somebody since I was three.
我从三岁起就是个 名声不怎么样的人。

211
00:09:16.924 --> 00:09:17.903
(Laughter)
（笑声）

212
00:09:17.903 --> 00:09:20.721
This is me on my third birthday.
这是我三岁生日时的照片。

213
00:09:20.743 --> 00:09:23.087
But I've been this girl all my life,
但我这一生从未改变，

214
00:09:23.111 --> 00:09:25.180
and I feel like even that's been the domino,
我始终觉得应该去当那一张骨牌，

215
00:09:25.204 --> 00:09:27.504
because in a world that wants us to walk around
因为上帝想让我们去

216
00:09:27.528 --> 00:09:29.368
as representatives of ourselves,
为自己发声，

217
00:09:29.392 --> 00:09:31.652
being yourself can be a revolutionary act.
活出自我是一种革命性的行为。

218
00:09:31.711 --> 00:09:34.599
And in a world that wants us to whisper,
在一个想让我们谨言慎行的世界里，

219
00:09:34.625 --> 00:09:36.179
I choose to yell.
我选择大声呼喊。

220
00:09:36.821 --> 00:09:41.807
(Applause)
（掌声）

221
00:09:41.831 --> 00:09:44.232
When it's time to say these hard things,
当我感到有些事情 让我难以启齿的时候，

222
00:09:44.256 --> 00:09:45.894
I ask myself three things.
我会问自己三个问题，

223
00:09:45.918 --> 00:09:47.757
One: Did you mean it?
第一：你是认真的吗？

224
00:09:48.329 --> 00:09:50.446
Two: Can you defend it?
第二：你可以为它辩护吗？

225
00:09:50.708 --> 00:09:53.074
Three: Did you say it with love?
第三：你是为爱发声吗？

226
00:09:53.188 --> 00:09:55.420
If the answer is yes to all three,
如果这三个问题的答案都是肯定的，

227
00:09:55.444 --> 00:09:57.301
I say it and let the chips fall.
我就会不计后果地说出来。

228
00:09:58.970 --> 00:10:00.139
That's important.
那很重要。

229
00:10:00.540 --> 00:10:02.065
That checkpoint with myself
这三个问题

230
00:10:01.905 --> 00:10:04.410
always tells me, "Yes, you're supposed to do this."
始终给予我肯定的力量。

231
00:10:06.415 --> 00:10:08.800
Telling the truth -- telling thoughtful truths --
说实话—— 说出深思熟虑的实话——

232
00:10:07.898 --> 00:10:09.785
should not be a revolutionary act.
不应该成为革命性的举动。

233
00:10:11.685 --> 00:10:15.133
Speaking truths to power should not be sacrificial, but they are.
对权势说真话不应该 意味着牺牲，但事实却是如此。

234
00:10:16.190 --> 00:10:19.378
But I think if more of us chose to do this for the greater good,
但是如果更多的人能加入我们，

235
00:10:19.402 --> 00:10:21.702
we'd be in better spaces than we are right now.
我们的处境会比现在更好。

236
00:10:22.803 --> 00:10:24.315
Speaking of the greater good,
说到更好的世界，

237
00:10:25.258 --> 00:10:28.690
I think we commit ourselves to telling truths to build bridges
我认为我们有责任 用真相搭建桥梁，

238
00:10:28.714 --> 00:10:30.191
to common ground,
去连接共同点，

239
00:10:30.215 --> 00:10:33.427
and bridges that aren't based on truth will collapse.
那些没有用真相 搭建起来的桥梁就会崩塌。

240
00:10:32.995 --> 00:10:35.163
So it is our job,
所以，这是我们的工作，

241
00:10:35.336 --> 00:10:38.664
it is our obligation, it is our duty
我们的义务和责任

242
00:10:38.688 --> 00:10:40.860
to speak truth to power, to be the domino,
不屈从于权贵，去成为骨牌，

243
00:10:41.703 --> 00:10:43.322
not just when it's difficult --
不只是在艰难的时候——

244
00:10:43.346 --> 00:10:45.335
especially when it's difficult.
尤其是在艰难的时候。

245
00:10:45.359 --> 00:10:46.553
Thank you.
谢谢。

246
00:10:46.577 --> 00:10:52.726
(Applause)
（掌声）